  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nOur linting CI job only runs on changes to `packages/**/*.ts` or `packages/**/*.ts`. However, we've learned that various random things can trigger linting errors. I'd like to propose that we run the linting job on *every* pull request. It's a relatively cheap job and it prevents a lot of developer headache.\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nI see two concrete ways of doing this:\r\n1. Modify [ts-packages.yml](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/master/.github/workflows/ts-packages.yml ) to be more permissive with the paths it will trigger on.\r\n2. Create a new job that triggers on *all* pull requests to master/release candidates.\r\n",
